    "The error bars include systematic errors resulting from the radioactive source's position and the peak extraction method.",
    "These measurements exhibited consistency across the crystals and the measuring techniques within the associated uncertainties.",
    "The well-known K-shell dip of NaI(Tl) at 33 keV is also identifiable.The data was fitted using an empirical function developed based on the Payne's model [15][16][17][18][19], as shown by the orange curve in Fig. 5.",
    "An expectation arises for the presence of the L-shell dip structure around 4.5 keV, although there is an insufficient number of data points below 20 keV to constrain the detailed shape of the dip.",
